style=3D"font-size: 1pt; color: =
white;"><o:p></o:p></span></div></div><p>Hi =
Grant,<o:p></o:p></p><p>Thank you for your recent email and for the =
summary of our meeting. I appreciate your efforts to move the claim =
forward.<o:p></o:p></p><p>There are a few important matters I=E2=80=99d =
like to clarify to ensure the process remains safe, fair, and aligned =
with Tower=E2=80=99s responsibilities under the =
policy.<o:p></o:p></p><p>First, regarding the items I took with me from =
the property =E2=80=94 including my electric vehicle (EV), laptops, =
tablets, and mobile phones =E2=80=94 these were all exposed to heat, =
smoke, and corrosive chemicals (including nearby spa products that =
intensified the fire). I remain concerned about internal damage, =
particularly to lithium batteries, and the potential for delayed failure =
or fire.<o:p></o:p></p><p>It is not appropriate or reasonable for Tower =
to shift the responsibility for assessing or managing the risk of these =
items to me. Ensuring they are safe for continued use is a critical =
safety issue =E2=80=94 not just a claims matter. Tower must take =
responsibility for confirming whether these items are safe, and whether =
they require restoration or replacement.<o:p></o:p></p><p>Second, I =
would appreciate clarification of Asset Restore=E2=80=99s scope. Is =
their role limited to cataloguing and removing contents, or will they =
also be undertaking removal of fire- or smoke-damaged linings (such as =
jib and other non-structural internal components)? This detail is =
important for understanding when and how a proper structural assessment =
of the property will take place.<o:p></o:p></p><p>Lastly, I would like =
to request a clear and updated plan for the progression of the house =
claim. Could you please provide:<o:p></o:p></p><ul type=3D"disc" =
style=3D"margin-bottom: 0in;"><li>A current status update on the =
structural assessment and any scoping completed to =
date;<o:p></o:p></li><li>A proposed timeline for the next phases: =
removal, scoping, approvals, tendering, and =
repair;<o:p></o:p></li><li>Confirmation of the parties responsible for =
each stage and how updates will be =
communicated.<o:p></o:p></li></ul><p>I look forward to your response =
addressing the points above.<o:p></o:p></p><p>Kind =
regards,<br>Rafaella<o:p></o:p></p><div class=3D"MsoNormal" =
align=3D"center" style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 12pt; font-family: =
Aptos, sans-serif; text-align: center;"><hr size=3D"2" width=3D"100%" =
align=3D"center"></div><p>Let me know if you want to attach the policy =
wording or include any references to specific =
clauses.<o:p></o:p></p><div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 12pt; =
font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><br><br><o:p></o:p></div><blockquote =
