font-family: Calibri, =
sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></div></div><div><div style=3D"margin: =
0in; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt;">I have spoken with both our Motor and our =
Claims Team Leaders, and they have said that the items you have enquired =
about are very unlikely to be affected by the fire given their location =
with respect to the proximity of the fire. I do understand that you =
would like to be 100% certain that the lithium batteries in these items =
have not been affected from the fire. The standard process in this =
situation is that you can undertake any testing of any of your items =
which you wish to, to obtain test results or a report which your insurer =
can consider for inclusion in your claims. If the test results prove any =
damage or loss to these items from the fire =E2=80=93 then your insurer =
will consider them within your claim.</span><span style=3D"font-size: =
11pt; font-family: Calibri, =
sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></div></div><div><div style=3D"margin: =
0in; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt;">&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, =
sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></div></div><div><div style=3D"margin: =
0in; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt;">For contents items - please direct your =
enquiries to<span class=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a =
